@startuml optic_batching_preflight

!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ncosta-ic/catppuccin-macchiato-plantuml-theme/main/theme.puml

title Two ways to ask a program "what would you do?"

participant "Caller" as C
participant "Fetch program" as P
participant "Runner" as R
participant "Backend" as B

== Online: Fetch.runCached (real I/O) ==
C -> R : runCached(program, resolver)
R -> P : pending()
P --> R : { id_1, ..., id_N }
R -> B : resolver({ id_1, ..., id_N })
B --> R : { id_1: v_1, ..., id_N: v_N }
R --> C : RunResult(value, rounds=1, fetchedBatches=[...])

== Offline: Plans.preflight (no I/O) ==
C -> R : preflight(program)
R -> P : pending()
P --> R : { id_1, ..., id_N }
note right of R
  Resume with stub nulls.
  No backend, no values,
  no side effects.
end note
R -> P : resume(stub map)
P --> R : Done (or another Blocked)
R --> C : Plan(fetchedBatches=[...], truncated=?)

@enduml
